# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Corpora — huge, and WSJ0 is LDC-licensed (not ours to redistribute).
# See README.md "Setup" for how to obtain and rebuild them.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
data/
data_src/
data_local/
*.tgz
*.tar.gz

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WSJ0-derived audio. Mixtures and references ARE WSJ0 speech; the estimates are
# derived works. Redistributing any of it would republish LDC93S6A.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
separated_wsj0/
demo_out/
demo_out_auto/
artifact.html
*.wav
*.flac

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Vendored upstream clones. SR_CorrNet_SS has its own upstream git history and a
# multi-GB venv; only our own patches are committed, under 6-speaker/.
# README.md's Setup section says how to re-clone it.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Our four 6-speaker patches under 6-speaker/SR_CorrNet_SS/ are already tracked,
# so this rule does not touch them -- it only stops a fresh upstream clone dropped
# in either location from being committed wholesale.
voice-seperation/SR_CorrNet_SS/
6-speaker/SR_CorrNet_SS/
tools/pywsj0-mix/
tools/ffmpeg-*/
tools/ffmpeg.zip

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Model weights and training output — regenerable, and far over GitHub's limits.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.pth
*.ckpt
*.pt
exp/
enroll_scp/

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
.venv-*/
*.egg-info/

# Run logs — noisy, and every result worth keeping is already in results_*.md
*.log

# Agent/editor scratch
.claude/
.cursor/
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
